<h2><strong>Tuesday</strong></h2>
<h3><span style="font-size: x-small; font-family: Calibri,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small; font-family: TimesNewRomanPSMT,sans-serif; color: #000000;">"I'm New here: Migration, Sexuality and Racism" Poetry, Film Screening and Discussion<br /></span></span></h3>
<p>Join us for an evening of poetry, videos and discussion on migration, sexuality and racism. &ldquo;I&rsquo;m New Here&rdquo; will include a viewing of short films and some photographs based on the experiences of queer, African migrants living in Winnipeg, and a lively discussion led by the project&rsquo;s filmmakers and researchers, Dr. Susan Frohlick and Irene Fubara-Manuel. In addition, local poets will contribute their artistic interpretations of the themes. We welcome all to attend this free, public event.This event is part of UBC Okanagan&rsquo;s Rule Out Racism Week. Rule Out Racism is a week-long series of events organized by the Equity and Inclusion Office focused on the need for greater literacy and conversation about race and racism within UBC and the surrounding communities where our students, staff and faculty call home.</p>
<p>Please contact <a href="mailto:equity.ubco@ubc.ca">equity.ubco@ubc.ca</a> for any questions. Light refreshments will be provided.</p>
